                   (Policeman H, 218). I produce a conviction—(Read:"Worship Street Police Court, June, 1857; James Stewart, Convicted, on his own confession, of stealing 5s. 5d. from the person; 
Confined Six Months")—the prisoner is the person; I had him in custody.

                  Aug., 1856, of stealing a watch and chain from the person; 
